Fyre is a tool for producing computational artwork based on histograms of
iterated chaotic functions. At the moment, it implements the Peter de Jong
map in a fixed-function pipeline with an interactive GTK+ frontend and a
command line interface for easy and efficient rendering of high-resolution,
high quality images.
